visualizations.description:
This chart displays the proportion of expected reporting subunits that completed and submitted the input form for reporting TB notification. Interpretation of TB notification trends relies greatly on consistent and complete reporting from the basic management units (BMUs). Use this chart to view the time periods when reporting from BMUs was not complete.
This is aggregated for user's organisation units with a period of the last 4 quarters.
visualizations.name: TB  - 10.1 Completeness and timeliness of notification report

visualizations.description: This chart displays the proportion of expected reporting subunits that completed and submitted the input form for reporting TB outcomes. Interpretation of TB notification trends relies greatly on consistent and complete reporting from the basic management units (BMUs). Use this chart to view the time periods when reporting from BMUs was not complete. This is aggregated for user's organisation units with a period of the last 4 quarters.
visualizations.name: TB  - 10.2 Completeness and timeliness of outcome report

visualizations.description:
This table displays a list of key data elements and the unit level completeness (%) in each of the last 4 quarters, for the user's org unit. 

Use this list to further interrogate the level of completeness in the past recent periods, of indicators being tracked for trend and geographical analysis. 

Indicators highlighted in red may be unreliable as fewer than nine in ten (<90%) of expected facilities have reported this data element. 

Completeness by a variable is calculated as (Count of reported values x100) / Count of actual reports for each report assigned
visualizations.name: TB  - 10.3 Completeness of quarterly reported data elements

This table displays a list of key data elements and the unit level completeness (%) in each of the last 4 quarters, for the user's org unit.

visualizations.name: TB  - 10.4 Completeness of annually reported data elements

visualizations.description: This table displays a list of key indicators and highlights those with validity concerns in each of the last 5 years, for subunits of the user's organisation unit. Indicators highlighted in red may need further interrogation to explore the cause of the inconsistency.
visualizations.name: TB  - 10.5 Internal consistency of selected indicators

visualizations.description: This chart shows the population at the subunit level for comparison of trends. The district-level user can check that the subunits are well configured and that there are no unexplained shifts in trends.
visualizations.name: TB - 10.09 Trends of population data

visualizations.description: This chart compares the cohort size for which DS outcomes have been reported, to the concurrent number of notifications. Use this concurrently with the line list above, to explore the reasons behind the loss of cohort members.  It is plotted for user's organisation units for a period of last 4 quarters.
visualizations.name: TB - 10.6 Trends of TB notification and outcomes for DS-TB cohort

visualizations.description: This chart displays to see if inconsistencies are due to recording and reporting concerns. It compares the number of new pulmonary bacteriologically confirmed with new tests for rifampicin susceptibility that should have a linear relationship and shows outliers for organisation units outside the threshold for outlier detection. . This is plotted for the user's sub-org units for last year.
visualizations.name: TB - 10.7 Scatter plot for new pulmonary bacteriologically confirmed vs New tests for rifampicin susceptibility

visualizations.description:
This chart shows the delta/changes in the annual notification rate trends over the past 5 years (green) and compares the trend against that of new, pulmonary, bacteriologically confirmed case notification rates (blue) in the last 5 years. They should be consistent.  
This is computed as a change in notification rate =  (TB notification rate this year - TB notification rate previous year )/ TB notification rate previous year
visualizations.name: TB - 10.8 Year-to-year percentage change in annual notification rates (%)
